		<p class="text">
			<b>National Energy Strategy:</b> Created in Mexico in 2012, it states that by 2026 Mexico must increase renewable energy generation from the current 4% in 2012 to 35% by the year 2026. This has created new opportunities in the renewable energy sector and enables foreign cleantech companies to expand to the Mexican market. Investors seeking opportunities in renewable energy, water innovation technologies and waste management outside the United States should consider Mexico as their next target market. Mexico has an abundance of renewable power resources and a keen awareness of the environmental and economic benefit of alternative energy development. 
		</p>

